            . I am a <rs id="t18300916-245-viclabel1252" type="occupation">surgeon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-245-victim2016 t18300916-245-viclabel1252"></join>, and live at No. 31, Upper Charlotte-street, Fitzroy-square. At eleven o'clock in the forenoon, on the 20th of July, I was in <placeName id="t18300916-245-crimeloc1253">St. James'-park</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-245-crimeloc1253" type="placeName" value="St. James'-park"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-245-crimeloc1253" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-245-off1250 t18300916-245-crimeloc1253"></join>, and lost my handkerchief at the review of the troops - I did not feel any thing, but a person told me my pocket had been picked; I turned round, and saw the officer with my handkerchief; the officer had one of the prisoners, and another person the other.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-245-person2018">
                  ANGELIOUS 
                  BETRAUN
               <interp inst="t18300916-245-person2018" type="surname" value="BETRAUN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-245-person2018" type="given" value="ANGELIOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-245-person2018" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at the review - I saw the prosecutor; the two prisoners were together behind him- Williams turned from him with a yellow handkerchief in his hand; I seized him - he threw himself on the ground, and endeavoured to put it between the feet of the people; Quick covered him while he took it - I took him and the handkerchief; another man took Quick.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183009160107"></xptr>Quick's Defence. All of a sudden this man came and laid hold of me, and charged me with stealing this handkerchief - my mistress, who was with me, stepped up and said I had nothing to do with it; she came to the office, but I was committed.</p>
               <p>Williams' Defence. I was going on an errand for my mother, and saw the handkerchief on the ground - I took it up; I never saw this boy before.</p>
